Tom don't have to try too hard to gain our acceptance.. he's got it... he earned it and he will always have it.  He don't have to try at all.. with me.<br>
One good thing about Tom, Art, SW, John, Joe, Chet and Cookie.. they both can bend a little... but not enough to kiss somebody's ass.<br>
Not true, however, with you.. you bend to extremes to unjustly criticise.. then bend the opposite direction to falsely partonize.  There are no limits ethical, moral or whatever in your attempts to control.. to drag everyone down to your low station.. a person who gained nothing from good fathers and grandfathers.. but instead received a lot of enablement in lieu of support.. a hollow soul, void of God who sought the pleasure principle and subscribed to the filth on the streets.  It's no wonder that you seek acceptance... demand acceptance.. when you are unworthy.  You are a man without boundries.. lost!<br>
We don't need any Hawkers or Cheerleaders on this site.  If Doc Del wants to appear or not appear so be it.  He don't need you as a front man.<br>
I can't throw you over my shoulders and run with you... I can't pluck you out of danger with a helicopter.. but I can and will try intercessory prayer.  If anyone ever needed rescuing..it's YOU!<br>
I have to laugh at your observation that Tom's morals have declined.<br>
I have to disagree with Cookie.. you haven't grown smaller.. you reached that limit a long time ago.  Instead, like Eyah the Campeater.. you have simply changed ploys.  Challenging combat veterans... laughing at God.. doesn't make you look tough.  To the world, or at least this site, you come across like a Chihuahua barking at a Pit Bull through the iron fence.  Wake up!  Someday the fence will disappear.<br>
My people would laugh at you and call you one who wants to be &quot;Wahanksica,&quot; an arrogant and overpowering grizzly bear.. they would laugh harder and say the when &quot;Yuha,&quot; the command to attack the enemy came.. you would change from a bear to &quot;Winkte,&quot; a man who wants to be a woman.<br><br>
I am Tatekohomni Wambli, a descendant of my fathers, Bull Elk, Wild Horse, Marshall Cho Cof Per Tsoko and Edward Cante Tinza (Brave Heart) Ramon.  I have touched the enemy.. I have killed the enemy... my children are safe.  I would feed your hair to the dogs before it would disgrace my lodge pole.  At the crossing of the river, the Creator will turn his back on you and hide his face from you!
